Thank you, Rudy for bringing up the subject of top-level domain "NET".
I can't help but to applaud the policy CSNET folks have set forward
on naming their hosts under domains other than domain "NET".  As Craig
correctly pointed out that one of the original objectives for the design
of this domain scheme is to move away from service dependent naming
in the Internet naming scheme.  The creation of top-level domain "NET"
is, in my opinion, counter-productive.  Would like to hear different
opinions or a decision from NIC to wind down the "NET" domain before
it is too late.

Zaw-Sing

